00:16:15,788 --> 00:16:17,039
[pained exhale]

266
00:16:18,624 --> 00:16:21,585
[cell phone vibrates]

267
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:28,426
CHAIRMAN AHN GYUSEOK

268
00:16:30,970 --> 00:16:33,389
[vibrating in armrest]

269
00:16:33,472 --> 00:16:34,932
[car engine turns over]

270
00:16:35,016 --> 00:16:36,309
Where are we going now?

271
00:16:38,352 --> 00:16:39,687
Somewhere safe.

272
00:16:40,855 --> 00:16:41,939
[Heeju exhales]

273
00:16:42,023 --> 00:16:45,026
[engine revving]

274
00:16:51,824 --> 00:16:52,867
[Officer] Hello, sir.

275
00:16:54,118 --> 00:16:56,954
Hey. Take this. Here.

276
00:16:57,038 --> 00:16:59,415
I caught this one over
at the dead drop earlier.

277
00:17:00,791 --> 00:17:03,085
Take it to, uh--what's it called?

278
00:17:03,169 --> 00:17:05,129
Narcotics for analysis.

279
00:17:05,212 --> 00:17:07,715
Oh, and also,
I'll tell the chief about it.

280
00:17:07,798 --> 00:17:09,175
Okay, understood.

281
00:17:17,683 --> 00:17:18,684
[Jinman] Sit over there.

282
00:17:28,778 --> 00:17:29,987
[Jinman exhales]
STYLE
::cue()

283
00:17:33,783 --> 00:17:35,159
[pained groan]

284
00:17:35,242 --> 00:17:37,036
[chair scraping]

285
00:17:39,205 --> 00:17:40,206
[scoffs]

286
00:17:41,707 --> 00:17:43,459
[Jinman] Now I might die because of you.

287
00:17:44,835 --> 00:17:45,920
Let's talk now.

288
00:17:46,879 --> 00:17:48,464
It's not too late.

289
00:17:49,215 --> 00:17:51,717
[Jinman] Look, I know how you feel, okay?

290
00:17:52,385 --> 00:17:55,763
Of course you want it.
It's so tempting, right?

291
00:17:56,305 --> 00:17:59,475
You don't have any idea what Chairman Ahn
is like, though.

292
00:18:00,976 --> 00:18:05,106
If you don't return the gold bars,
you and I are both going to die.

293
00:18:06,232 --> 00:18:07,692
[Jinman] What's more important to you?

294
00:18:08,275 --> 00:18:09,902
The gold bars or your life?

295
00:18:11,237 --> 00:18:13,406
I can't give the chairman back his gold.

296
00:18:14,782 --> 00:18:17,201
Because Lee Dokyung already took half.

297
00:18:17,993 --> 00:18:19,620
[Heeju] So I only have half left.

298
00:18:21,330 --> 00:18:22,581
[Jinman exhales sharply]

299
00:18:22,665 --> 00:18:23,666
Fuck.

300
00:18:23,749 --> 00:18:24,750
[clicks tongue]

301
00:18:24,834 --> 00:18:25,835
[fist bangs on table]

302
00:18:27,253 --> 00:18:28,629
[chair scrapes]

303
00:18:34,301 --> 00:18:35,886
[exhales]

304
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:40,766
[sighs]

305
00:18:43,728 --> 00:18:48,065
If that's the case,
we'll return half for now, yeah?

306
00:18:48,858 --> 00:18:50,860
And we'll catch Lee Dokyung after.

307
00:18:51,819 --> 00:18:53,779
Do you think Chairman Ahn
will believe that?

308
00:18:54,613 --> 00:18:57,908
Don't you think he would suspect that
you kept the other half for yourself?

309
00:18:59,326 --> 00:19:01,078
[Heeju] If that happens...

310
00:19:01,579 --> 00:19:04,582
...you'll have no choice but
to tell him my name eventually.

311
00:19:04,665 --> 00:19:06,333
[Jinman] I said I wouldn't tell him.

312
00:19:06,417 --> 00:19:07,418
Okay?

313
00:19:09,503 --> 00:19:12,339
You already saw when I was on
the phone earlier talking to Chairman Ahn.

314
00:19:12,423 --> 00:19:13,924
[Jinman] I won't tell him about you.

315
00:19:15,301 --> 00:19:16,510
Where are they?

316
00:19:18,429 --> 00:19:19,847
Why are you trying so hard

317
00:19:19,930 --> 00:19:22,099
to give Chairman Ahn back his gold,
anyway?

318
00:19:23,517 --> 00:19:24,852
Isn't it obvious?

319
00:19:25,644 --> 00:19:26,771
Huh?

320
00:19:26,854 --> 00:19:29,106
Chairman Ahn is the owner
of that gold.

321
00:19:29,482 --> 00:19:31,358
[Heeju] Once you make me talk...

322
00:19:32,234 --> 00:19:34,653
...you'll just try and keep all
the gold for yourself.

323
00:19:35,863 --> 00:19:37,615
That's what all the others tried to do.

324
00:19:38,866 --> 00:19:40,075
Park did that.

325
00:19:40,534 --> 00:19:41,702
Cha Yujin, too.

326
00:19:42,995 --> 00:19:46,081
Have you considered that maybe I'm not
as greedy as they are?

327
00:19:48,417 --> 00:19:50,503
[inhales deeply]

328
00:19:53,464 --> 00:19:55,257
It's not about greed.

329
00:19:55,341 --> 00:19:57,134
You just don't have the courage for it.

330
00:19:58,177 --> 00:20:00,554
The courage to fight Chairman Ahn and win.

331
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,349
[Heeju] You're just too scared of him.

332
00:20:05,392 --> 00:20:07,144
How much did he promise to give you?

333
00:20:09,188 --> 00:20:10,940
That's none of your business.

334
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,566
I'll double the amount.

335
00:20:14,860 --> 00:20:15,986
[Heeju] Detective.

336
00:20:17,363 --> 00:20:19,615
I'm the one who has
the gold bars right now.

337
00:20:20,157 --> 00:20:23,244
Which means I'm the real owner
of the gold, not Chairman Ahn.

338
00:20:23,744 --> 00:20:26,831
So if you wanna get your payment,
it isn't Ahn you need.

339
00:20:26,914 --> 00:20:28,666
I'm the one you should make a deal with.

340
00:20:31,585 --> 00:20:33,671
You're a real nut.
You know that?

341
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:35,381
Huh?

342
00:20:36,382 --> 00:20:38,926
It's like you've totally lost your mind.

343
00:20:39,426 --> 00:20:40,970
[Jinman] You'd better snap out of it, kid.

344
00:20:42,096 --> 00:20:43,973
The gold bars aren't the issue right now.

345
00:20:44,890 --> 00:20:48,143
It's that the two of us are gonna die.

346
00:20:48,227 --> 00:20:50,729
If I die,
it's because of you.

347
00:20:50,813 --> 00:20:51,814
[Jinman] Because of you!

348
00:20:52,606 --> 00:20:54,817
And my life is more important to me.

349
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,318
[exhales]

350
00:20:56,402 --> 00:20:58,404
[Jinman] What good is the gold
if you're dead?

351
00:21:00,322 --> 00:21:04,118
I would rather die than live that way.

352
00:21:06,787 --> 00:21:08,205
[Jinman] What?

353
00:21:09,540 --> 00:21:10,583
What'd you say?

354
00:21:12,376 --> 00:21:13,919
I would rather be dead...

355
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,672
...than live like you people.
STYLE
::cue()

356
00:21:23,095 --> 00:21:24,346
HEEJU

357
00:21:24,430 --> 00:21:27,433
[cell phone vibrating]

358
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:34,023
[panicked breathing]

359
00:21:36,191 --> 00:21:37,192
Hello?

360
00:21:38,152 --> 00:21:39,612
[Jinman] Hey, did you take care of it?

361
00:21:42,573 --> 00:21:43,574
Yeah.

362
00:21:45,242 --> 00:21:48,329
Uh, how's Heeju?

363
00:21:49,038 --> 00:21:50,372
[Jinman] That's none of your business.

364
00:21:51,457 --> 00:21:54,460
From now on, don't even think about
setting foot in Jeongsan ever again.

365
00:21:55,419 --> 00:21:56,462
And as for Kim Heeju...

366
00:21:57,546 --> 00:21:59,381
...I need you to stay away from her.

367
00:22:00,090 --> 00:22:02,384
[Jinman] If I ever catch you
hanging around Jeongsan again...

368
00:22:03,135 --> 00:22:04,261
...then I swear...

369
00:22:04,845 --> 00:22:06,138
...I will kill you.

370
00:22:07,264 --> 00:22:08,265
Got it?

371
00:22:08,349 --> 00:22:10,559
I--if anything happens to Heeju...

372
00:22:12,061 --> 00:22:13,062
...I'll kill you, too.

373
00:22:14,271 --> 00:22:15,731
I--I'll tell them everything.

374
00:22:16,607 --> 00:22:18,859
[Woogy] Chairman Ahn, Park Hocheol,
the police.

375
00:22:18,943 --> 00:22:20,277
I'll even tell the police everything.

376
00:22:20,945 --> 00:22:22,279
As you wish.

377
00:22:22,363 --> 00:22:25,282
[Woogy] Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait! Wait. Detective, wait.

378
00:22:26,367 --> 00:22:28,911
If I--if I give you the gold bars...

379
00:22:29,703 --> 00:22:30,788
...will you free Heeju?

380
00:22:31,330 --> 00:22:33,540
Did you find where they're hidden?
You know where they are?

381
00:22:35,292 --> 00:22:37,795
[nervous breathing]

382
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:41,090
Uh, first things first.

383
00:22:41,173 --> 00:22:42,424
Could I speak to Heeju?

384
00:22:42,508 --> 00:22:43,509
[Jinman] Are you serious?

385
00:22:43,592 --> 00:22:44,593
[phone disconnects]

386
00:22:47,054 --> 00:22:48,389
[exhales]

387
00:22:48,472 --> 00:22:49,723
Shit.

388
00:22:50,099 --> 00:22:51,141
[exhales sharply]

389
00:22:55,396 --> 00:22:56,438
Sir.

390
00:22:56,522 --> 00:22:58,148
-Hmm?
-Someone's looking for you.

391
00:22:58,232 --> 00:22:59,233
Hmm?

392
00:23:03,904 --> 00:23:05,114
[Jo] Hello.

393
00:23:05,197 --> 00:23:06,740
Detective Kim.

394
00:23:09,118 --> 00:23:11,036
[inhales]

395
00:23:12,413 --> 00:23:13,664
So what happened?

396
00:23:15,582 --> 00:23:17,835
I was up all night long waiting for you.

397
00:23:19,128 --> 00:23:23,757
Well, I caught Ju Haran and we
were heading to where the mine is located.

398
00:23:23,841 --> 00:23:26,176
Then some car just suddenly hit us
from behind and we--

399
00:23:26,260 --> 00:23:27,302
[Ahn] Enough.

400
00:23:28,012 --> 00:23:29,221
Get to the point.

401
00:23:30,389 --> 00:23:31,724
So you lost her.

402
00:23:32,349 --> 00:23:33,851
And the casket, too.

403
00:23:34,435 --> 00:23:35,978
Yeah.

404
00:23:36,061 --> 00:23:37,771
You don't know whose car it was?

405
00:23:38,397 --> 00:23:40,524
I think the car was Park Hocheol's.

406
00:23:41,775 --> 00:23:43,861
Seems like Yes Money
is working with him now.

407
00:23:43,944 --> 00:23:45,195
[Ahn scoffs]

408
00:23:46,238 --> 00:23:47,406
Gitae, too?

409
00:23:49,491 --> 00:23:50,743
[exhales sharply]

410
00:23:51,326 --> 00:23:53,037
I don't know how much
of this I should believe

411
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,246
and how much I shouldn't.

412
00:23:54,329 --> 00:23:56,206
Just give me a few--no.

413
00:23:56,957 --> 00:23:58,167
Just give me one more day.

414
00:23:58,250 --> 00:23:59,960
I'm tracking the car through
surveillance footage.

415
00:24:00,044 --> 00:24:01,045
I know I'll find it soon.

416
00:24:03,047 --> 00:24:04,673
Look, Kim Jinman.

417
00:24:05,174 --> 00:24:08,218
[Jinman] Do you know why I never
told Hocheol about the gold bars?

418
00:24:09,428 --> 00:24:10,679
The truth is,

419
00:24:10,763 --> 00:24:13,432
I was never able
to get any collateral on that man.

420
00:24:14,725 --> 00:24:16,727
The people with something to protect...

421
00:24:17,519 --> 00:24:19,772
...they wouldn't even dream
of betraying me.

422
00:24:19,855 --> 00:24:23,150
[Ahn] Whether it's their child,
their life, money, or beliefs.

423
00:24:23,233 --> 00:24:25,235
Most people don't want
to lose those things.

424
00:24:25,319 --> 00:24:26,528
They're worth too much.

425
00:24:26,612 --> 00:24:28,906
But Park,
he doesn't have anything like that.

426
00:24:28,989 --> 00:24:32,618
But I don't have anything
that's worth protecting.

427
00:24:32,701 --> 00:24:35,788
Your ex-wife.
What was her name, again?

428
00:24:36,121 --> 00:24:37,122
Yeo Sunok.

429
00:24:38,123 --> 00:24:39,333
[Ahn] She's in the hospital.

430
00:24:39,792 --> 00:24:41,293
[Ahn laughs]

431
00:24:41,376 --> 00:24:42,961
You abandoned your wife.

432
00:24:43,337 --> 00:24:45,422
Yet you're still doing whatever it takes.

433
00:24:45,506 --> 00:24:48,258
I guess you're trying
to hold onto what you have left.

434
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:51,970
[Ahn] And you're just really desperate
to stay alive.

435
00:24:53,430 --> 00:24:56,767
Sure, why not wait one more day?

436
00:24:57,893 --> 00:25:00,020
I promise I'll find the gold bars.

437
00:25:01,230 --> 00:25:02,898
I'll do whatever it takes, sir.

438
00:25:04,149 --> 00:25:06,693
Just give me one gold bar
like you said you would.

439
00:25:07,653 --> 00:25:10,739
That way I can finally start living
a decent life.

440
00:25:10,823 --> 00:25:12,908
[chuckles]

441
00:25:14,409 --> 00:25:15,410
Okay.

442
00:25:28,549 --> 00:25:30,050
[lighter flicks]

443
00:25:30,134 --> 00:25:31,468
[inhales on cigarette]

444
00:25:39,226 --> 00:25:42,229
[machines hissing and beeping]

445
00:25:44,982 --> 00:25:46,108
[exhales sharply]
STYLE
::cue()

446
00:25:48,819 --> 00:25:49,945
Hey, Sunok.

447
00:25:51,613 --> 00:25:54,116
No matter how many times I try
to save your daughter...

448
00:25:54,908 --> 00:25:56,702
...she just won't listen.

449
00:25:58,537 --> 00:26:01,081
Who do you think she got that from,
I wonder?

450
00:26:03,625 --> 00:26:05,169
[inhales sharply]

451
00:26:09,548 --> 00:26:10,716
[grunts]

452
00:26:18,557 --> 00:26:19,558
Hey.

453
00:26:22,603 --> 00:26:23,687
Yeah.

454
00:26:25,939 --> 00:26:27,858
Uh, what?

455
00:26:30,402 --> 00:26:32,654
Uh, this? Huh?

456
00:26:33,363 --> 00:26:34,406
[Jinman] Okay.

457
00:26:37,492 --> 00:26:39,203
-Heeju.
-Huh?

458
00:26:39,828 --> 00:26:41,246
Where's Heeju?

459
00:26:41,788 --> 00:26:45,584
Oh, yeah. She--she's okay.
I've got her. She's fine.

460
00:26:47,794 --> 00:26:49,338
[inhales weakly]

461
00:26:49,421 --> 00:26:50,631
She's...

462
00:26:52,174 --> 00:26:55,385
...she's not like us, is she?

463
00:26:56,136 --> 00:26:58,055
Oh, yeah, yeah.
She's not.

464
00:26:59,264 --> 00:27:00,265
[grunts]

465
00:27:01,850 --> 00:27:02,851
Let...

466
00:27:03,602 --> 00:27:05,145
[pained inhale]

467
00:27:05,896 --> 00:27:09,233
...let her live the way she wants to.

468
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:16,031
Let her go her own way.

469
00:27:16,114 --> 00:27:17,574
Mm-hmm.

470
00:27:19,826 --> 00:27:24,665
You and I already lived our lives.

471
00:27:28,585 --> 00:27:29,628
Mm-hmm.

472
00:27:31,922 --> 00:27:33,048
[inhales]

473
00:27:39,513 --> 00:27:40,764
Jinman.

474
00:27:43,517 --> 00:27:44,726
[inhales]

475
00:27:44,810 --> 00:27:47,562
Thank you, Jinman.

476
00:27:52,651 --> 00:27:54,361
[Sunok] Thank you.

477
00:27:56,071 --> 00:27:57,406
[exhales]

478
00:27:59,116 --> 00:28:01,576
I'm gonna rest now.

479
00:28:05,956 --> 00:28:07,374
[inhales]

480
00:28:08,333 --> 00:28:10,419
[mask hisses]

481
00:28:22,431 --> 00:28:25,434
[machines beeping]

482
00:28:48,832 --> 00:28:49,875
[Jinman gasps]

483
00:28:58,383 --> 00:28:59,676
[lightly sobs]

484
00:29:07,768 --> 00:29:10,771
[crying]

485
00:29:14,441 --> 00:29:16,026
I'm so sorry.

486
00:29:20,489 --> 00:29:21,740
Ah, shit.

487
00:29:28,955 --> 00:29:31,958
[crying]

488
00:29:39,132 --> 00:29:42,135
[♪ dramatic music]

489
00:29:50,227 --> 00:29:51,353
[Mija gasps]

490
00:29:51,436 --> 00:29:52,562
[Mija] No.

491
00:29:53,188 --> 00:29:54,189
Sunok.

492
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:56,650
Sunok!

493
00:29:59,027 --> 00:30:00,195
Sunok.

494
00:30:00,278 --> 00:30:02,114
[crying]

495
00:30:02,197 --> 00:30:03,532
Sunok.

496
00:30:04,658 --> 00:30:05,992
Sunok.
STYLE
::cue()

497
00:30:15,377 --> 00:30:22,384
YES MONEY

498
00:30:23,969 --> 00:30:26,596
[car door opens]

499
00:30:28,098 --> 00:30:29,516
[exhales]

500
00:30:32,144 --> 00:30:33,436
[Gitae sighs]

501
00:30:40,485 --> 00:30:41,736
Whoa.

502
00:30:43,655 --> 00:30:45,407
[Gitae] What brings you all the way here?

503
00:30:47,325 --> 00:30:48,785
Have a seat.

504
00:30:51,621 --> 00:30:52,956
Go ahead.
Sit down.

505
00:30:54,082 --> 00:30:55,542
You want a tea or something?

506
00:30:57,878 --> 00:30:59,337
[groans]

507
00:31:05,218 --> 00:31:06,219
[Jinman] Hey.

508
00:31:07,512 --> 00:31:10,348
I told your guys that I wanted them out
of the hospital.

509
00:31:11,850 --> 00:31:13,101
They didn't tell you?

510
00:31:13,185 --> 00:31:16,271
[laughs]

511
00:31:16,354 --> 00:31:18,273
Why do you keep doing this?

512
00:31:18,356 --> 00:31:20,108
They can't even go to the hospital?

513
00:31:20,192 --> 00:31:22,360
They were all there
to see the doctor.

514
00:31:22,444 --> 00:31:24,654
I didn't come here
to joke around, asshole.

515
00:31:27,324 --> 00:31:28,325
[clears throat]

516
00:31:34,831 --> 00:31:36,208
Whose side are you on?

517
00:31:36,833 --> 00:31:39,544
Chairman Ahn or Park Hocheol?

518
00:31:40,712 --> 00:31:42,297
What's that supposed to mean?

519
00:31:44,132 --> 00:31:45,634
Hey, this is Yes Money!

520
00:31:45,717 --> 00:31:48,553
And the Chairman owns Yes Money
so obviously I'm on his side.

521
00:31:49,095 --> 00:31:50,222
Are you sure?

522
00:31:51,306 --> 00:31:52,849
Yeah, of course I am.

523
00:31:54,142 --> 00:31:57,520
So Chairman Ahn sent those guys
to the hospital then, right?

524
00:31:58,939 --> 00:32:00,482
[Jinman] Give the Chairman this message.

525
00:32:01,816 --> 00:32:03,193
You can pull all your guys out.

526
00:32:07,530 --> 00:32:09,616
Because Yeo Sunok is dead now.

527
00:32:19,918 --> 00:32:21,836
[door creaks]

528
00:32:27,509 --> 00:32:29,094
[Henchman] Yes.
We'll take you in this car.

529
00:32:35,642 --> 00:32:37,519
-Thank you.
-Oh. Thank you very much.

530
00:32:37,602 --> 00:32:38,937
[camera shutters clicking]

531
00:32:55,954 --> 00:32:56,955
[golf club clinks]

532
00:32:57,038 --> 00:32:58,415
-[Caddie] Good shot!
-[Board Member] Good shot.

533
00:32:58,498 --> 00:33:00,709
[clapping]

534
00:33:05,755 --> 00:33:06,756
[golf club clinks]

535
00:33:07,173 --> 00:33:09,342
-[Board Member] Oh, nice shot.
-[Caddie] Wow, nice shot.

536
00:33:09,426 --> 00:33:12,470
[clapping]

537
00:33:14,931 --> 00:33:17,642
[Jinman] Excuse me! Hello.
Excuse me.

538
00:33:19,019 --> 00:33:20,103
[Jinman grunts]

539
00:33:20,687 --> 00:33:22,272
Hello there. Hi.

540
00:33:22,355 --> 00:33:23,398
[inhales]

541
00:33:23,481 --> 00:33:26,359
Sorry, give me one second.

542
00:33:26,443 --> 00:33:27,777
Hang on here.

543
00:33:28,945 --> 00:33:33,700
Yes, excuse me. I wanted to ask,
are you guys from Cambodia, by any chance?

544
00:33:34,117 --> 00:33:35,160
[Dictation App speaking Cambodian]

545
00:33:35,243 --> 00:33:38,663
Here. Look.
You can read this.

546
00:33:38,747 --> 00:33:39,748
Who are you?

547
00:33:40,749 --> 00:33:42,375
Shit, you guys know how
to speak Korean?

548
00:33:43,251 --> 00:33:45,045
[Jinman] So you must have seen this,
right?

549
00:33:45,837 --> 00:33:48,298
He's the governor, you know, huh?

550
00:33:48,381 --> 00:33:49,549
This guy. It's him.

551
00:33:49,632 --> 00:33:50,842
-Mr. Ahn.
-Oh.

552
00:33:50,925 --> 00:33:51,926
So glad you could make it.

553
00:33:52,260 --> 00:33:53,595
-[Socom] Nice to meet you. Hello.
-How do you do?

554
00:33:53,678 --> 00:33:55,263
-Congratulations.
-[Socom] Thank you.

555
00:33:55,347 --> 00:33:56,806
All these people here...
STYLE
::cue()

556
00:33:57,349 --> 00:33:58,892
...all of them are fake.

557
00:33:59,392 --> 00:34:00,518
Okay?

558
00:34:01,353 --> 00:34:03,355
So you came here in the middle
of the game?

559
00:34:03,438 --> 00:34:05,523
Who told you that absolute nonsense?

560
00:34:05,607 --> 00:34:06,608
[laughs]

561
00:34:06,691 --> 00:34:09,027
All I've heard is that he's one
of the Geumseong guys.

562
00:34:09,110 --> 00:34:11,029
Could you describe what he looked like?

563
00:34:11,654 --> 00:34:14,157
Did he have a scar anywhere on his face?

564
00:34:16,493 --> 00:34:17,786
[inhales]

565
00:34:17,869 --> 00:34:19,412
Park Hocheol.

566
00:34:20,789 --> 00:34:22,290
That idiot.

567
00:34:22,374 --> 00:34:24,417
I knew he'd try something eventually.

568
00:34:26,294 --> 00:34:27,754
How about this?
The governor.

569
00:34:27,837 --> 00:34:30,423
If you're suspicious,
do you wanna go see him?

570
00:34:30,507 --> 00:34:31,966
In person, I mean.

571
00:34:32,050 --> 00:34:34,427
[Geonggang] We don't fully trust that man,
either.

572
00:34:36,971 --> 00:34:38,014
We just...

573
00:34:39,140 --> 00:34:41,935
...we want to know if the gold bars
are kept safe.

574
00:34:42,018 --> 00:34:44,771
Well, did you report it yet?

575
00:34:44,854 --> 00:34:46,064
[inhales]

576
00:34:46,147 --> 00:34:47,148
[exhales]

577
00:34:47,232 --> 00:34:48,233
Not yet, no.

578
00:34:48,316 --> 00:34:49,859
[inhales]

579
00:34:50,652 --> 00:34:52,237
Okay, then.

580
00:34:57,117 --> 00:34:58,952
CALLING
YES MONEY KO GITAE

581
00:34:59,536 --> 00:35:02,122
[phone trilling]

582
00:35:02,205 --> 00:35:03,498
[receiver clicks]

583
00:35:03,581 --> 00:35:04,791
Hey, President Ko.

584
00:35:05,667 --> 00:35:07,961
Our Cambodian guests have asked me
if it's possible

585
00:35:08,044 --> 00:35:09,546
to show them the casket today.

586
00:35:10,213 --> 00:35:11,589
Could you take care of it?

587
00:35:11,673 --> 00:35:14,676
[indistinct chatter]

588
00:35:22,308 --> 00:35:23,309
[spits]

589
00:35:29,899 --> 00:35:31,151
[Gitae] Afternoon, sir.

590
00:35:31,693 --> 00:35:32,736
We're all ready to go.

591
00:35:36,823 --> 00:35:39,826
[car rumbling]

592
00:35:50,253 --> 00:35:52,255
Where are we going?

593
00:35:52,756 --> 00:35:54,591
You wanted to see the casket, right?

594
00:35:55,884 --> 00:35:56,885
We're almost there.

595
00:35:57,385 --> 00:35:58,470
[laughs]

596
00:36:05,518 --> 00:36:06,770
[tires squeak]

597
00:36:06,853 --> 00:36:10,899
[distant crows cawing]

598
00:36:10,982 --> 00:36:14,235
[inhales and exhales]

599
00:36:17,405 --> 00:36:18,573
President Ko.

600
00:36:19,824 --> 00:36:21,201
You sure it's here?

601
00:36:21,743 --> 00:36:23,912
I think so. I haven't been out here
in a while, though.

602
00:36:24,829 --> 00:36:26,331
Is it this way?

603
00:36:27,457 --> 00:36:29,250
Hey, this the right place?

604
00:36:30,335 --> 00:36:31,461
[phone trilling]

605
00:36:31,544 --> 00:36:33,421
-[Gitae] Then why..
-This is Socom.

606
00:36:34,672 --> 00:36:36,841
[Socom] No, we're still in Jeongsan.

607
00:36:36,925 --> 00:36:38,343
[glass shatters]

608
00:36:38,426 --> 00:36:40,136
[all grunting]

609
00:36:40,220 --> 00:36:42,180
[Gitae] You scared me!
Shit. Fucking hell.

610
00:36:43,056 --> 00:36:46,059
[blades slicing]

611
00:36:46,810 --> 00:36:48,353
Whoa. Hey, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

612
00:36:48,436 --> 00:36:50,396
[all groaning]

613
00:36:50,480 --> 00:36:51,397
[glass shatters]

614
00:36:51,481 --> 00:36:52,816
[screaming]

615
00:36:52,899 --> 00:36:53,983
[blow lands]

616
00:36:54,067 --> 00:36:55,151
[blades slicing]

617
00:36:55,235 --> 00:36:57,153
[all grunting]

618
00:36:57,237 --> 00:36:59,531
[shouting]

619
00:37:04,869 --> 00:37:06,955
[blows landing]
[groaning]

620
00:37:15,380 --> 00:37:16,464
[thuds]

621
00:37:22,637 --> 00:37:24,514
President Ko.

622
00:37:25,390 --> 00:37:28,935
[Cheonggang] Tell Chairman Ahn to bring
the casket right away.

623
00:37:29,018 --> 00:37:30,019
Yes, sir.

624
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:31,896
[Cheonggang grunts]

625
00:37:33,731 --> 00:37:35,608
Oh, shit. We're really fucked.

626
00:37:35,692 --> 00:37:37,235
[nervous breathing]

627
00:37:37,318 --> 00:37:38,862
We're so fucked.
STYLE
::cue()

628
00:37:43,575 --> 00:37:46,578
[crickets chirping]

629
00:37:46,953 --> 00:37:49,706
[phone trilling]

630
00:37:49,789 --> 00:37:52,125
DIRECTOR PARK HOCHEOL

631
00:37:52,208 --> 00:37:55,211
[cell phone vibrating]

632
00:37:55,295 --> 00:37:56,963
[inhales sharply]

633
00:37:57,046 --> 00:37:59,924
-Hello, sir.
-[Hocheol] Did you find that prick Woogy?

634
00:38:01,050 --> 00:38:02,468
Well, he got away from us.

635
00:38:03,177 --> 00:38:04,596
Finding him isn't easy.

636
00:38:07,140 --> 00:38:09,183
What about the jewelry store? What?

637
00:38:09,851 --> 00:38:10,935
Nothing from them yet?

638
00:38:11,477 --> 00:38:13,354
[Gitae] No, not yet.

639
00:38:13,438 --> 00:38:17,066
He was last seen over at Lucky Jewelry.
He was selling the gold there.

640
00:38:18,234 --> 00:38:19,652
It's him for sure.

641
00:38:19,736 --> 00:38:22,906
[Gitae] Choi, the owner,
he sent me the surveillance footage.

642
00:38:24,032 --> 00:38:26,951
That prick will show up again.
He's still got gold to sell.

643
00:38:27,869 --> 00:38:30,455
[Hocheol] Tell him to stay alert.
Watch carefully.

644
00:38:31,456 --> 00:38:33,583
[Gitae] Yeah, will do.

645
00:38:34,500 --> 00:38:36,336
My boys are keeping an eye on the place.

646
00:38:38,129 --> 00:38:42,759
If I hear anything from Lucky Jewelry,
or anywhere else,

647
00:38:42,842 --> 00:38:44,177
I'll let you know right away, sir.

648
00:38:44,260 --> 00:38:48,598
LUCKY JEWELRY

649
00:38:55,355 --> 00:38:57,148
LUCKY JEWELRY, DAEJEONG

650
00:38:57,231 --> 00:39:02,028
LUCKY JEWELRY

651
00:39:07,116 --> 00:39:10,119
[cell phone vibrating]

652
00:39:15,416 --> 00:39:18,711
[vibrating continues]

653
00:39:26,469 --> 00:39:27,470
[Dokyung] Heeju.

654
00:39:30,223 --> 00:39:32,100
Is this Lee Dokyung?

655
00:39:34,227 --> 00:39:36,688
Bet it is. Yeah.

656
00:39:36,771 --> 00:39:38,481
Lee Dokyung, am I right?

657
00:39:39,774 --> 00:39:41,442
This is the police calling.

658
00:39:41,526 --> 00:39:43,987
I'm detective Kim Jinman
with Investigations.

659
00:39:46,364 --> 00:39:49,075
I heard you're in possession
of half of the gold bars.

660
00:39:53,955 --> 00:39:54,956
Are you listening?

661
00:39:56,165 --> 00:39:57,208
Good.

662
00:39:58,084 --> 00:39:59,836
Right now we're holding Kim Heeju.

663
00:40:01,754 --> 00:40:03,423
But, I think we can release her.

664
00:40:04,173 --> 00:40:05,633
We should make a deal.

665
00:40:06,634 --> 00:40:07,760
[Dokyung] Where should I go?

666
00:40:12,348 --> 00:40:15,727
Uh, you know that street in Daejeong
with all the jewelry stores?

667
00:40:16,894 --> 00:40:18,938
[Jinman] There's a shop called
Lucky Jewelry there.

668
00:40:19,022 --> 00:40:22,275
You can sell your gold bars.
They take them at that store, 'kay?

669
00:40:24,152 --> 00:40:28,322
Once you're finished with all that,
make sure you give me a call immediately.

670
00:40:28,406 --> 00:40:30,575
I'll give you
a meeting location afterwards.

671
00:40:32,035 --> 00:40:33,161
[Jinman] See you tomorrow.

672
00:40:33,244 --> 00:40:34,495
[call disconnects]

673
00:40:34,579 --> 00:40:41,586
JG JANGGAK TRADE INC

674
00:40:41,711 --> 00:40:43,254
[cell door clanging]

675
00:40:43,337 --> 00:40:44,422
[creaks]
STYLE
::cue()

676
00:40:54,265 --> 00:40:55,808
[groans]

677
00:40:56,476 --> 00:40:58,728
[sniff and exhales sharply]

678
00:41:01,105 --> 00:41:02,106
How is it in here?

679
00:41:05,860 --> 00:41:07,278
I'm gonna release you now.

680
00:41:07,945 --> 00:41:09,947
Leave by the end of the day.
Take the gold, too.

681
00:41:12,450 --> 00:41:14,118
Actually, you know what?

682
00:41:14,202 --> 00:41:15,453
Forget about the gold.

683
00:41:16,245 --> 00:41:17,538
You just need to get out of here.

684
00:41:19,165 --> 00:41:20,583
Don't go to the hospital.

685
00:41:22,794 --> 00:41:24,420
Don't go to the pawnshop, either.

686
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:30,134
Chairman Ahn's out there,
looking all over Jeongsan to find you.

687
00:41:30,218 --> 00:41:31,511
He has guys everywhere.

688
00:41:34,263 --> 00:41:35,431
Why did you...

689
00:41:37,934 --> 00:41:39,143
What happened?

690
00:41:40,436 --> 00:41:42,438
You just suddenly changed your mind?

691
00:41:43,314 --> 00:41:44,398
[smacks lips]

692
00:41:44,482 --> 00:41:45,900
I've been, uh...

693
00:41:47,068 --> 00:41:48,653
...I've been thinking about it.

694
00:41:51,823 --> 00:41:54,117
And you might've had
the right idea all along.

695
00:41:56,202 --> 00:41:59,956
Instead of returning all the gold bars
to Chairman Ahn just for peanuts...

696
00:42:00,915 --> 00:42:01,916
...I was thinking...

697
00:42:02,750 --> 00:42:05,586
...I should just work out a
good deal with you directly.

698
00:42:06,337 --> 00:42:07,964
[Jinman] You said it yourself.

699
00:42:08,047 --> 00:42:11,259
Right now you're the one
with the gold bars, right?

700
00:42:12,051 --> 00:42:13,094
[Jinman] That's what you said.

701
00:42:15,429 --> 00:42:16,848
How much will you give me?

702
00:42:18,224 --> 00:42:19,517
How much do you want?

703
00:42:21,352 --> 00:42:24,730
Well, you said you'd double what
the Chairman offered.

704
00:42:25,690 --> 00:42:26,816
I want 20, then.

705
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:28,609
He originally offered to give me 10.

706
00:42:30,570 --> 00:42:31,821
[Jinman] Let's go.

707
00:42:31,904 --> 00:42:33,489
No.

708
00:42:33,573 --> 00:42:35,575
Forget it.
I'll stay right here in this cell.

709
00:42:36,576 --> 00:42:38,286
You can just send me to prison.

710
00:42:41,330 --> 00:42:42,331
Fine.

711
00:42:43,666 --> 00:42:45,626
Be like that, then, huh?

712
00:42:46,460 --> 00:42:48,671
And never trust anybody
in this world who isn't you.

713
00:42:50,506 --> 00:42:52,049
What a great way to live.

714
00:42:52,717 --> 00:42:53,759
[exhales]

715
00:42:54,260 --> 00:42:56,512
[Jinman] Give me two, then.
Just two.

716
00:42:57,847 --> 00:42:59,932
I can live with two gold bars.

717
00:43:00,016 --> 00:43:02,560
He only offered me one.
So give me two.

718
00:43:03,227 --> 00:43:04,228
We have a deal?

719
00:43:04,687 --> 00:43:06,063
Here.

720
00:43:06,147 --> 00:43:07,607
[Jinman exhales]

721
00:43:13,362 --> 00:43:14,822
Hey, why don't you try pulling
your hands out?

722
00:43:14,906 --> 00:43:16,616
[Jinman] They look small enough
to slip out.

723
00:43:17,366 --> 00:43:18,784
No. No, they won't.

724
00:43:18,868 --> 00:43:20,203
[groans]

725
00:43:20,286 --> 00:43:21,329
Come on.

726
00:43:23,289 --> 00:43:25,458
I guess they're not that small.

727
00:43:25,541 --> 00:43:26,876
[exhales]

728
00:43:26,959 --> 00:43:29,629
[handcuffs clinking]

729
00:43:30,755 --> 00:43:32,048
[exhales]

730
00:43:34,675 --> 00:43:35,801
[Jinman] Here.

731
00:43:36,969 --> 00:43:37,970
These are your things.

732
00:43:41,599 --> 00:43:45,228
I already spoke to Woogy
and Lee Dokyung over the phone.

733
00:43:46,896 --> 00:43:49,023
I told them you're being held
at the police station.

734
00:43:49,941 --> 00:43:51,651
You won't get any calls
from those two.

735
00:43:52,026 --> 00:43:55,821
And even if they try to reach you,
don't ever pick up the phone.

736
00:43:56,530 --> 00:43:57,573
[Jinman] You can be tracked.

737
00:43:58,491 --> 00:43:59,492
Got it?
STYLE
::cue()

738
00:44:00,076 --> 00:44:04,789
JEONGSAN POLICE ALWAYS
SERVES YOU WITH CARE

739
00:44:07,416 --> 00:44:08,542
[groans]

740
00:44:12,171 --> 00:44:13,714
In my glove box,
there's a gun.

741
00:44:15,258 --> 00:44:16,717
It's there if you need it.

742
00:44:18,135 --> 00:44:21,555
But you better not use it unless
it's absolutely necessary.

743
00:44:22,098 --> 00:44:23,140
Understand?

744
00:44:24,475 --> 00:44:25,476
Okay.

745
00:44:26,018 --> 00:44:27,770
Thank you very much.

746
00:44:27,853 --> 00:44:29,230
No need to thank me for this.

747
00:44:29,313 --> 00:44:31,565
Just give me my gold bars
before you leave.

748
00:44:31,649 --> 00:44:33,776
[Jinman] I'm not kidding.
I'll tell everyone.

749
00:44:38,572 --> 00:44:39,782
[car alarm beeps]

750
00:44:44,495 --> 00:44:45,496
[car door closes]

751
00:44:47,581 --> 00:44:50,251
[car engine turns over]

752
00:44:52,378 --> 00:44:53,379
Hey, sir?

753
00:44:55,798 --> 00:44:57,300
Look after Sunok for me.

754
00:44:59,885 --> 00:45:01,220
[gold clangs]

755
00:45:05,308 --> 00:45:08,311
[car engine rumbling]

756
00:45:21,699 --> 00:45:22,700
[clinks]

757
00:45:26,203 --> 00:45:27,204
[zipper unzips]

758
00:45:39,175 --> 00:45:40,301
[gold clinks]

759
00:45:44,930 --> 00:45:46,057
YES MONEY KO GITAE

760
00:45:46,140 --> 00:45:47,558
CALLING...
YES MONEY KO GITAE

761
00:45:47,641 --> 00:45:50,644
[phone trilling]

762
00:45:52,271 --> 00:45:53,397
[Gitae] What's goin' on?

763
00:45:53,647 --> 00:45:55,066
Is Park still in contact with you?

764
00:45:55,816 --> 00:45:58,027
[Gitae] Do you think I have a death wish?
I'm not crazy.

765
00:45:58,944 --> 00:46:01,072
I know you're acting,
so just cut the bullshit.

766
00:46:01,155 --> 00:46:02,281
[clicks tongue]

767
00:46:02,365 --> 00:46:03,783
Give Park this message.

768
00:46:04,950 --> 00:46:06,494
I can help catch Lee Dokyung.

769
00:46:06,577 --> 00:46:08,120
And if he finds the casket...

770
00:46:08,996 --> 00:46:10,081
...I want a billion.

771
00:46:11,499 --> 00:46:13,042
No, no, no.
Two billion.

772
00:46:13,125 --> 00:46:14,835
Two billion sounds good, 'kay?

773
00:46:16,087 --> 00:46:17,296
[Jinman] I won't wait for long.

774
00:46:21,425 --> 00:46:22,635
[phone chimes]

775
00:46:22,718 --> 00:46:25,721
[phone trilling]

776
00:46:28,307 --> 00:46:30,267
Hello, Chairman. Yes.

777
00:46:31,268 --> 00:46:32,853
I finally found Lee Dokyung.

778
00:46:33,479 --> 00:46:35,481
And we might as well take care
of Park Hocheol

779
00:46:35,564 --> 00:46:36,899
at the same time, if we can.

780
00:46:37,983 --> 00:46:42,196
I'll have President Ko send his guys
to, uh, Lucky Jewelry tomorrow, okay?

781
00:46:43,197 --> 00:46:44,740
I'll make sure everyone's there.

782
00:46:52,915 --> 00:46:54,083
[car parks]

783
00:46:54,166 --> 00:46:55,501
[seat belt unbuckles]

784
00:47:01,048 --> 00:47:02,425
Three.
STYLE
::cue()

785
00:47:07,805 --> 00:47:09,056
[breathing heavily]

786
00:47:09,140 --> 00:47:11,350
When's the earliest boat out
of the country leaving?

787
00:47:11,434 --> 00:47:12,977
I don't care where it's going.

788
00:47:13,978 --> 00:47:17,189
The first boat would be the one
the day after tomorrow.

789
00:47:17,690 --> 00:47:20,025
Why are you asking all of a sudden?
Did something happen?

790
00:47:20,109 --> 00:47:21,152
I need a ticket.

791
00:47:21,235 --> 00:47:24,196
For a car and a passenger,
like the last one.

792
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:26,699
Yeah, I can do that.
Who's getting on the boat?

793
00:47:27,408 --> 00:47:28,534
[grunts]

794
00:47:28,617 --> 00:47:29,660
I will.

795
00:47:29,743 --> 00:47:30,828
Huh?

796
00:47:31,287 --> 00:47:32,955
What on Earth is going on here?

797
00:47:33,539 --> 00:47:36,083
Are you both gonna travel separately on
the same boat?

798
00:47:37,501 --> 00:47:38,502
What?

799
00:47:38,586 --> 00:47:42,590
Well, your boyfriend came by earlier
and he asked me for a ferry ticket, too.

800
00:47:43,299 --> 00:47:46,594
[Donggu] He wanted a ticket for himself
and one car, just like you.

801
00:47:46,677 --> 00:47:48,095
And he bought his car here.

802
00:47:51,599 --> 00:47:53,559
[car engine rumbling]

803
00:48:09,658 --> 00:48:12,661
[car engine rumbling]

804
00:48:29,345 --> 00:48:30,387
[Woogy] If I...

805
00:48:30,679 --> 00:48:33,891
...if I give you the gold bars,
will you free Heeju?

806
00:48:37,144 --> 00:48:38,270
Shit.

807
00:48:47,655 --> 00:48:48,656
[Woogy groans]

808
00:48:48,739 --> 00:48:49,782
Fuck.

809
00:48:55,037 --> 00:48:57,206
[crickets chirping]

810
00:48:57,289 --> 00:48:58,916
[exhales sharply]

811
00:49:02,294 --> 00:49:03,546
[exhales]

812
00:49:07,550 --> 00:49:08,551
[phone chimes]

813
00:49:08,634 --> 00:49:10,135
[phone trilling]

814
00:49:10,803 --> 00:49:11,804
Hello?

815
00:49:11,887 --> 00:49:14,223
[Woogy] Hello, sir, this is Woogy.

816
00:49:14,306 --> 00:49:16,308
-Hello?
-[Woogy] I'm sorry.

817
00:49:16,392 --> 00:49:18,519
Sir, please, help me.

818
00:49:18,602 --> 00:49:20,187
[Woogy] I'll explain everything.

819
00:49:20,271 --> 00:49:21,438
[Moonsu] Where are you?

820
00:49:21,897 --> 00:49:23,983
[Woogy] I--I'm in the barn.

821
00:49:24,066 --> 00:49:25,234
[Moonsu] The barn?

822
00:49:25,317 --> 00:49:26,318
[Woogy] Yes.

823
00:49:26,735 --> 00:49:28,362
Okay. Just hold on, then.

824
00:49:28,445 --> 00:49:29,780
I'll be right there.

825
00:49:29,863 --> 00:49:31,156
[Woogy] Okay.

826
00:49:31,657 --> 00:49:33,826
-I appreciate it.
-[Moonsu] Sure.

827
00:49:33,909 --> 00:49:35,327
That asshole Woogy's at the barn.

828
00:49:35,411 --> 00:49:36,579
-Let's go. Come on.
-Let's get out of here.

829
00:49:36,662 --> 00:49:38,163
[car engine turns over]

830
00:49:39,540 --> 00:49:41,875
[car engine revving]

831
00:49:45,671 --> 00:49:47,131
[engine humming]

832
00:49:51,510 --> 00:49:54,513
[engine rumbling]

833
00:49:55,514 --> 00:49:56,515
[tires squeak]

834
00:49:58,601 --> 00:50:01,604
[car engine revs]
STYLE
::cue()

835
00:50:12,031 --> 00:50:13,324
[door lock clicks]

836
00:50:13,407 --> 00:50:16,410
[door creaks]

837
00:50:24,501 --> 00:50:26,754
[door clatters]

838
00:50:58,577 --> 00:51:00,996
[door creaks]

839
00:51:23,227 --> 00:51:24,228
[door creaks]

840
00:51:29,650 --> 00:51:31,110
[Woogy exhales]

841
00:51:31,193 --> 00:51:32,861
[Woogy] Fuck, it's here.

842
00:51:37,658 --> 00:51:38,659
[door clangs]

843
00:51:38,742 --> 00:51:39,743
[gasps]

844
00:51:41,870 --> 00:51:43,789
[door squeaking]

845
00:51:49,253 --> 00:51:50,587
[gold bars clinking]

846
00:51:59,930 --> 00:52:01,014
[metal clinks]

847
00:52:08,522 --> 00:52:09,523
[inhales sharply]

848
00:52:17,865 --> 00:52:19,116
Captain?

849
00:52:21,076 --> 00:52:22,327
The fuck?

850
00:52:22,411 --> 00:52:24,163
What are you doing here?

851
00:52:24,246 --> 00:52:25,414
I can explain.

852
00:52:25,497 --> 00:52:27,332
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

853
00:52:28,500 --> 00:52:31,795
It's Heeju.
She's been arrested.

854
00:52:32,254 --> 00:52:34,214
[Woogy breathing heavily]

855
00:52:34,882 --> 00:52:36,675
[metal clinks on floor]

856
00:52:36,759 --> 00:52:38,302
I'm Heeju's childhood friend.

857
00:52:38,761 --> 00:52:40,387
[Woogy] And her business partner.

858
00:52:40,471 --> 00:52:42,139
The bars. The bars!
I helped her.

859
00:52:42,222 --> 00:52:44,683
I was the one who sold the bars.
I did that.

860
00:52:44,767 --> 00:52:45,976
Cut the crap and shut up.

861
00:52:46,518 --> 00:52:48,312
Go and grab the gold bars.
Move it!

862
00:52:48,395 --> 00:52:49,730
No, hold on!

863
00:52:49,813 --> 00:52:51,523
We don't have time for this, huh?

864
00:52:51,982 --> 00:52:54,777
We need to use those gold bars
to get Heeju out of the police station.

865
00:52:55,277 --> 00:52:57,780
[Woogy] Detective Kim Jinman.
You know who he is, right?

866
00:52:58,447 --> 00:52:59,990
He works for the Geumseong guys.

867
00:53:00,574 --> 00:53:01,825
Yeah?

868
00:53:01,909 --> 00:53:03,619
If we don't get her out
and if she doesn't confess,

869
00:53:03,702 --> 00:53:05,829
he'll hand her over to Geumseong
and Chairman Ahn and his thugs.

870
00:53:05,913 --> 00:53:06,914
[Dokyung] Cut the bullshit.

871
00:53:06,997 --> 00:53:10,000
I'm not gonna listen to some asshole
that's been blinded by all this gold.

872
00:53:10,501 --> 00:53:12,711
[Dokyung] Take them out. Now!

873
00:53:13,629 --> 00:53:14,838
[Woogy] Fine.

874
00:53:15,506 --> 00:53:16,924
We really don't have time for this shit.

875
00:53:20,886 --> 00:53:23,263
What the fuck, captain? Huh?

876
00:53:23,347 --> 00:53:24,973
You already have half
the fucking gold bars.

877
00:53:25,057 --> 00:53:26,725
You really had to come back for more?

878
00:53:28,060 --> 00:53:29,478
Shut your mouth.

879
00:53:30,187 --> 00:53:31,647
-Keep looking.
-I am looking.

880
00:53:32,147 --> 00:53:33,899
I don't know where they could be, either,
for fuck's sake.

881
00:53:35,901 --> 00:53:37,236
[Woogy groans]

882
00:53:37,319 --> 00:53:38,612
[Woogy] I'm lookin'!

883
00:53:38,695 --> 00:53:39,822
Just wait a second.

884
00:53:44,243 --> 00:53:45,577
[water running]

885
00:53:45,661 --> 00:53:48,664
[both grunting]

886
00:54:03,887 --> 00:54:07,015
[banging]
STYLE
::cue()

887
